OL,4,CBill concessions after talks with
OL,5,Crebels
OL,7,FExisting claimants were to be given a
OL,8,F13-week, phase-out period of financial
OL,9,Fsupport in an earlier move that was
OL,10,Fseen as a bid to head off opposition
OL,11,Fby aiming to soften the impact of the
OL,12,Fchanges.
OL,14,FHowever, concessions offered by the
OL,15,FGovernment to save the Bill from
OL,16,Fdefeat are understood to include a
OL,17,Fcommitment that those currently
OL,18,Freceiving Pip will continue to get the
OL,19,Fallowance.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/16
