OL,7,FRebels had also been calling for
OL,8,Fministers to row back on a freeze in
OL,9,Fthe health element of universal
OL,10,Fcredit, which was expected to lead to
OL,11,Fa #450 real decline in support for
OL,12,Fsome 2.2 million existing claimants.
OL,14,FIt is understood that the Government
OL,15,Fhas agreed to avoid such a reduction
OL,16,Fin support, as well as committing to a
OL,17,Ffuture consultation that would involve
OL,18,Ftaking the views of disabled people
OL,19,Fabout policy into account.
